@startuml
title Use Case 5: Starting a New Conversation

actor User
boundary GUI as "Client GUI"
control Client as "Client App"
control Server as "Server"
collections ClientCache as "Client Cache\n(User directory + Conversation headers)"
collections Store as "Server Persistent Storage\n(Message Data)"

ref over User, GUI, Client, Server : Searching For A User

== Create conversation ==
User -> GUI: Select one users\nClick "Start Conversation"
GUI -> Client: CreateConversation(participantUserIds)

Client -> Server: CreateConversation(participants)
Server -> Store: Create conversation file\n(conversationId, participants)
Store --> Server: Created (conversationId)
Server --> Client: CreateConversation OK\n(conversation object)

Client -> ClientCache: Add conversation object
Client --> GUI: Open new conversation view\n(conversation object)
@enduml
